& [CurrentAttentionRuntimeRegistryState] is the live semantic registry for active attention
  + [registry_status] is active
  + [registry_scope] is diversified LM Studio SOP worker task corpus
  + [active_root_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_lmstudio_task_corpus_001
  + [active_frame_count] is 1
  + [suspended_frame_count] is 0
  + [closed_frame_count] is 0
  + [return_anchor] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [registry_outside] is hidden activations, exact transformer attention, model weights, worker mutation authority, broad task competence, and unrelated Pinky worktree changes

  = must: update this state when focus materially changes
  = must: preserve return anchors before closing or suspending frames
  = must: keep the registry semantic and visible, not native-runtime or hidden-state based
  = should: stay compact enough for context-compression re-entry

& [AttentionFrame_2026_06_24_LMStudioTaskCorpus001] is the active semantic stack frame for the diversified LM Studio worker task corpus
  + [frame_id] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_lmstudio_task_corpus_001
  + [frame_state] is active
  + [parent_frame] is none
  + [child_frame_set] is functional_lmstudio_lane, one_minute_heartbeat, operating_loop_tick_005, task_corpus_009, corpus_queue_next, commit_receipt
  + [return_anchor] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [frame_trace] is LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus.sop, lm_studio_worker_task_corpus_20260624_009.sop, LMStudioWorkerFunctionalLane.sop, LMStudioAgentBenchmark.sop, 2026-06-24_operating_loop_tick_005.sop, and CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [focus_register] is six-family diversified corpus for LM Studio worker readiness
  + [question_register] is how to compile first diversified task-frame launch queue candidates
  + [delineation_register] is inside task_families, minimum_pass_gate, failure_gate, validation_gate, diversity_gate, and corpus_outside
  + [periphery_register] is corpus-not-proof, broad competence outside, project-root authority outside, validator gate, and unrelated dirty files outside
  + [operation_register] is define_task_corpus, update_lane_contracts, emit_corpus_event, emit_tick_005, update_reentry_state
  + [evidence_register] is LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus.sop, corpus event 009, six task families, and operating_loop_tick_005
  + [wisdom_register] is corpus diversity must be defined before readiness claims broaden
  + [caution_register] is unlaunched corpus tasks are future probes, not worker competence evidence
  + [balance_register] is stable because corpus boundaries, failure gates, and outside are explicit
  + [integration_register] is pending commit, push, and first diversified launch queue compilation
  + [frame_outside] is hidden model state, broad local-worker readiness, worker file mutation, remote claims before push, and unrelated workspace changes

  = must: treat this frame as current visible attention state
  = must: return clock_state, proof_state, balance_state, drive_state, next_step, and outside to CurrentFocalPoint when this focus pass closes
  = should: open child frames only when a concrete benchmark, scoring, or worker-profile pass is needed

(current_attention_runtime_registry_state) :active_root_frame: /semantic_register_set and return_anchor/ |registry_outside|
